-- Gasquet, Halep Win Kremlin Cup Tennis Titles; Ferrer Upset
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-10-20T18:08:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-20/gasquet-and-halep-win-kremlin-cup-tennis-titles-haas-victory.html
Richard Gasquet  of France recovered
to defeat Kazakh qualifier Mikhail Kukushkin in the Kremlin Cup
tennis final today. World No. 3  David Ferrer  was upset by Grigor
Dimitrov in the final of the Stockholm Open.  World No. 10 Gasquet, the top seed, won 4-6, 6-4, 6-4 in a
match lasting almost 2 1/2 hours. Romania’s Simona Halep, the
fifth seed, won the women’s event, defeating seventh-seed
Samantha Stosur of Australia 7-6 (7-1), 6-2.  Bulgaria’s Dimitrov, ranked 28th in the world, defeated
Spain’s Ferrer 2-6, 6-3, 6-4 for his first ATP Tour title.  Germany’s Tommy Haas beat Robin Haase of the Netherlands 6-3, 4-6, 6-4 in the Erste Bank Open final in Vienna. He also won
the competition 12 years ago.  Denmark’s  Caroline Wozniacki , the top seed, beat unseeded
Annika Beck of Germany 6-2, 6-2 in the Luxembourg Open final.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chris Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  